# Mangodoro — Roadmap / TODO

The strategy crystallized into THREE programs (+ cross-cutting polish). Two
"layers": the RECORD layer is what a team pays for (monetization); the RHYTHM
and BREAK layers get people in and coming back daily (engagement / cohesion).
"Park it" (below) is the bridge — it serves both.

Don't hard-pivot: the moat is the synchronous, multiplayer, cross-device focus
engine. These programs re-position AROUND that engine. Keep everything opt-in /
IC-owned / non-surveillance.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## ▶ BUILD NEXT  (highest leverage, cherry-picked across programs)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Notification LAYER — reusable infra (prefs + delivery surfaces + triggers).
   Foundational: powers awareness pings, break/park-it reminders, rejoin
   nudges, @mentions. Build as a platform, not one-offs.
2. "Park it" — pre-break snapshot / pick up where you left off (the "time to
   park & take a break" nudge rides on #1).   [keystone]
3. Whiteboard improvements — edge reliability (make it feel right >80% of the
   time) + table-stakes (undo/redo, copy/paste, image nodes, export).
4. Break deck (restorative) + ONE co-op break game on the whiteboard canvas
5. Pomodoro → timesheet auto-logging   (the record falls out of focusing)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## PROGRAM A — The work record   (monetization layer)
"You just focus; the recap / standup / timesheet write themselves."
(ordered by build sequence)
- [keystone] "Park it" pre-break snapshot — capture the NEXT action + parked
  context at break start (the one moment the user WANTS to type, so the
  friction pays for itself). On return: "you were…; next…; jump in?" Restore
  surfaces (open board, linked task) where possible. Doubles as the highest-
  quality work-record capture signal.
- Native session task / intention widget (replaces the stubbed Tasks widget) —
  "what I'm working on this session", one-tap, tied to a project/task.
- Pomodoro → timesheet auto-logging — completed focus time → time entries.
- AI day/week recap — summarize sessions + intentions + goals + chat into the
  end-of-day recap / standup (reuse DeepSeek). Summary is the EASY part —
  invest in capture quality ("confirm, don't compose"; capture only at seams).
- Later sources: ClickUp (suggested intentions from assignments), calendar
  (meetings auto-appear in the record).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## PROGRAM B — Collective rhythm   (get people focusing together)
The "company metronome" — but self-healing across time zones, opt-in /
invitational, never mandated.
- Notification LAYER [foundational — build FIRST] — a reusable delivery layer
  (push + desktop + in-app) with per-user preferences and a trigger system, so
  every other feature fires notifications without re-plumbing. Powers:
  awareness ("teammate started a focus session / joined Room X / is back from
  lunch"), "notify me when [person] starts focusing", @mention pings, AND the
  reminders for Program A (park-it / break) and Program C (break nudges).
  Build on the existing iOS push infra.
- Focus waves — start a wave others can SEE and JOIN; presence-driven, not a
  fixed global clock. (Minimal experiment: can a few people start a wave that
  others ride? Build on existing sync sessions.)
- Scheduled / recurring co-working sessions — reliable anchor blocks per
  time-zone cluster so there's always a "next wave" to rejoin.
- Lunch as a first-class status + self-healing rejoin — "out for lunch, back
  ~1:00"; when a critical mass returns, nudge "Maria & Tom are starting at :00
  — join?"; on YOUR return: "5 focusing, next break in 12 min — jump in?"
- "Join me" / invite a teammate to your current room (deep link + ping).
- Personal 1:1 calls — call a teammate directly (needs presence + notifs).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## PROGRAM C — Own the break   (engagement / cohesion / retention)
Nobody makes the break first-class — it's dead countdown time everywhere else.
Make it restorative, social, and fun; the team breaks in rhythm too.
- Break deck — activities sized to break length:
    · Restorative (short breaks): guided stretch, breathing, 20-20-20 eye
      rest, posture / hydrate nudges. (Wellbeing / anti-burnout angle.)
    · Co-op (long breaks): quick multiplayer games on the whiteboard canvas
      (doodle / Pictionary first — cheap on infra you already have), trivia,
      "this or that" icebreakers.
  GUARDRAIL: games HARD-STOP when the break ends; refreshing ≠ stimulating.
- Team-shared streaks + unlocks — the engagement loop. TEAM-shared, not
  individual (no Duolingo guilt; survives time zones / days off); streak
  freezes; celebrate milestones, never punish lapses. Unlocks: cosmetic by
  default (badges, team trophy, new break games, room themes) + OPTIONAL
  admin-funded real reward (e.g. a "pizza party" an admin configures & pays for).
- Inter-department co-op challenges — LAST, once the loop is proven. Compete on
  PARTICIPATION / consistency / hitting a shared goal — NOT raw hours (which
  rewards overwork and punishes different roles & schedules).
- Shared media widget — YouTube / music player (shared lo-fi while you work).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Cross-cutting QoL   (slot in opportunistically)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Whiteboard
SHIPPED: undo/redo · copy/paste/cut · image nodes (Storage) + drag-drop/paste ·
markdown in sticky/text/shape · easier resize + edge handles · text-selection
inside nodes (nodrag) · snap-on-resize · grow-to-fit (shape + STICKY) ·
double-click canvas → text · per-node text colour/align/B-I/bg/radius/padding ·
Google Fonts · z-order · lock node · per-node opacity · multi-select
align/distribute/match-size · persist viewport · export PNG · freehand pen ·
laser pointer (+ fading ink + colour) · interactive task checkboxes · alt-drag
clone · dot-voting on nodes · comments on nodes · collaborative RASTER paint
layer (infinite tiled, persisted).
- Export SVG / PDF (PNG done)
- Comments: per-node thread is flat + last-writer-wins on concurrent adds —
  an append-only log would harden it
- Paint follow-ups: viewport-priority tile load; tile manifest to skip list()
- Edge tuning (parked): side-flip hysteresis, detour cost, parallel-edge fan-out

### Video
- Keyboard shortcuts (mute, camera, screen share)
- Use the ROOM chat next to video (provider-agnostic); LiveKit has no chat
- LiveKit parity: reactions (reuse emote system) + raise hand
- Push-to-talk

### Rooms
- Room chat, make it sticky: @mentions (+ notification → feeds Program B),
  reactions (reuse emote system), unread badge / ping, image paste, pagination
- Deeper room settings (in-room ⚙️ shipped): topic/description, capacity,
  default layout, permissions
- Room topic / status visible from the hallway
- Idle auto-away; hallway favorites / sort

### Pomodoro / Time tracking
- Focus intention prompt at session start (feeds Program A)
- Per-session custom duration (without editing global settings)
- Idle detection / "log your time" nudge
- Calendar / heatmap view of logged time

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Larger / dependent builds
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Guest access + waiting room (merges guest-video + guest-room; auth/security)
- Integrations — Slack (post "team is focusing" / presence → Program B),
  ClickUp (task source → Program A)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Niche / future / heavy
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Whiteboard teleport / portal nodes
- Whiteboard presentation / follow mode (presenter drives everyone's viewport)
- Video recording / transcription / captions (heavy — LiveKit egress)
- Screen-share annotation
- Breakout rooms

## Dropped / folded (redundant with existing features)
- Temporary room type → use Meeting rooms (auto-close duration already exists)
- Lucide flowchart widget → covered by the existing whiteboard panel

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Positioning / the sell   (still TBD, converging)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Not "a pomodoro clock that links to tools." Leading frame: the team focuses
TOGETHER (rhythm), the BREAK is the best part (engagement), and the work
RECORDS ITSELF (monetization). "Park it" bridges fun → record. The untraveled,
team-only-ownable angle: collective focus rhythm where the timer protects flow
and the break is where cohesion happens — all opt-in / IC-owned / non-surveillance.
